2013-07-07 14:00  gespinasse

	* make.sh: Really fix unmounting shm on stdumount when /dev/shm is
	  a symlink to /run/shm like debian v7
	  It does not work to test if ${LFS}/dev/shm is mounted and I find
	  no other way than counting how many time /run/shm is mounted.
	  If the number is greater than 1, assume it's our script that
	  mount bind shm and it is needed to umount.
	  
	  Add a comment why the umount is conditional as ./make.sh clean
	  doesn't mount
	  
	  On machines that have /dev/shm as symlink, it is required to fix
	  sudo configuration

