	  Upgrade dosfstools to 3.0.14
	  Fix the download URL
	  Remove the upstream patch

2013-02-09 00:56  gespinasse

	* make.sh: The sudo -l | wc -l trick doesn't work on Centos-5.9 as
	  more than one command may be in a same line.
	  Instead use sudo -ll so each command is in a separate line.
	  
	  Fix SUDO_NUMBER to match the number of Cmnd_Alias defined
	  
	  Use -U with user name, so we are at least listing to the lines we
	  want to consider.
	  
	  It is no more required for an unconfigured user in sudoers to
	  type enter until failure of the sudo prompt.
	  The trick allowing that is to ask the password from standard
	  input with standard input closed ;-)

2013-02-07 07:32  gespinasse

	* lfs/libcap, lfs/pcmciautils, lfs/udev: Change kernel.org mirror
	  to find again the old files released before the attack

2013-02-06 13:32  gespinasse

	* lfs/openssl: Upgrade openssl to 1.0.1d
	  For us, that should fix CVE-2013-0169,CVE-2013-0166
	  To my understanding, we are not yet using AESNI code, so
	  CVE-2012-2686 (fixed by 1.0.1d) should not be an issue.

