	  So there is no loss keeping 'make check' commented out for now.

2012-11-23 22:36  gespinasse

	* lfs/linux: Remove the gettext hack
	  The sed is a wrong solution, actually produce static inline const
	  char *(const char *txt) function declaration
	  And the issue in the past should have been only with uClibc and
	  linux<2.6.15

2012-11-23 07:05  gespinasse

	* lfs/linux, lfs/linux-headers,
	  src/patches/linux-3.0_atm-headers.patch: Remove sed -i -e
	  's/-O2/-Os/g'
	  This is useless, CC_OPTIMIZE_FOR_SIZE=y is already there for the
	  code running on the target.
	  The few lines that don't use -Os (so -O2) are for code running on
	  the host during compilation only.
	  
	  Remove the last line that patch something in atm-headers.patch
	  This is a very old change (from 2.6.20) and nothing different
	  appear in log when the patch is removed
	  
	  Tested on 3.4.19, should be the same on 3.0.x

2012-11-21 21:55  gespinasse

