2012-07-30 15:55  gespinasse

	* lfs/beep, lfs/mdadm, updates/2.1.0/ROOTFILES.i486-2.1.0: Parsing
	  the log with something like
	  grep -rE 'gcc | cc ' log_i486 | grep -v ' -O' | grep -v checking
	  >mylog
	  
	  and discounting every link command, I find that mdmadm and beep
	  have no optimization level set, so with 0, FORTIFY did not apply.
	  
	  Unfortunately scanelf did not check for fortify yet but that
	  could be done manually with
	  readelf -sW <file> | grep -v '__stack_chk_fail' | grep '__.*_chk'

