2012-06-19 17:59  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/gzip, lfs/gzip,
	  src/patches/gzip-1.3.3-window-size.patch,
	  updates/2.1.0/ROOTFILES.i486-2.1.0,
	  updates/2.1.0/information.xml: Upgrade gzip to 1.5
	  
	  Remove gl_cv_func_printf_directive_n=no woraround as gnulib has
	  been fixed
	  Remove the Fedora patch that was droped in 2007 ('remove useless
	  patches' commit)
	  
	  Use DEFS="NO_ASM" for multiple reasons :
	  - we were lucky gzip-1.4 configure fail on 'checking for an
	  assembler syntax supported by this package' or make would have
	  failed later,
	  - asm cause textrel issue in our gcc configuration,
	  - Fedora use DEFS="NO_ASM", saying gcc compiled code is faster
	  than asm code
	  
	  Update the rootfile, as referring to man pages, not installed
	  since install-exec usage

2012-06-19 12:29  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/automake, lfs/automake: Upgrading
	  automake to 1.12.1
	  That fix the test suite that autoconf-2.69 upgrade may have
	  broken

