2012-01-19 08:19  dotzball

	* html/cgi-bin/urlfilter.cgi, langs/ipcop.new.en.pl,
	  src/libs/scheduler-lib.pl, src/rc.d/rc.updatered,
	  src/scripts/blacklistupdate.pl, src/scripts/scheduler.pl,
	  updates/2.0.3/ROOTFILES.i486-2.0.3: Remove Cron code stuff. The
	  blacklist update can now be called by scheduler or
	  when red interface connects (like the ipcop update list). May
	  needs some more
	  tweaking.
	  
	  The instant blacklist update by webui now fully moves the update
	  process in
	  background, no more timeout while waiting the update to finish.
	  
	  It is no longer possible to upload a custom redirect background
	  image. If user
	  wants to use an own image he can can manually copy a file named
	  custom-redirect-background.png to /home/httpd/html/images.
	  
	  The (new) lang text is currently not in the lang files, will
	  commit this later.

