2012-01-08 17:56  gespinasse

	* lfs/gnupg, src/patches/gnupg-1.4.11_call-gcc.patch: While testing
	  what will be gnupg-1.4.12, I find we dont need Fedora patch.
	  
	  Just adding 'LDFLAGS += -pie' fix the TEXTREL issue, and
	  --disable-asm is not required.
	  Unsure why I haven't been able to reproduce the issue with asm
	  code, maybe this was fixed with a binutils upgrade?
	  
	  Add again --enable-noexecstack so stack could be read only.
	  
	  1.4.12 should be made soon.

