	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl: Add code for a corner case where
	  NEXT_SWITCH_HOUR/MINUTE would not be set correctly.

2011-09-11 08:01  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/coreutils, lfs/coreutils,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Upgrade coreutils to 8.13, that
	  fix minor issues in chown, chgrp, cp, printf
	  
	  Remove the -N on patching uname, we want an error if an issue
	  happen applying the patch
	  
	  The move on usr/lib/coreutils/libstdbuf.so to
	  usr/libexec/coreutils/libstdbuf.so is intentional to fix an issue
	  with a futur automake release.
	  Let us not care that much as we do not use that file.

2011-09-08 06:20  gespinasse

	* lfs/gdb: I was too slow to commit 7.3 upgrade.
	  During that time, 7.3 was replaced by 7.3a and 7.3.1 has been
	  released, so upgrade to 7.3.1.
	  
	  Only 28 failures with 7.3.1 when building from my debian v6
	  (squeeze). That should be good enought for us.

2011-09-07 19:41  dotzball

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Fix check(s) for timeframe rules.
	  
	  Fixes SF bug #3403666

2011-09-07 06:45  gespinasse

	* lfs/gdb: Upgrade gdb to 7.3.
	  This fix the test suite on more recent distrib (for example
	  switching from debian v5 lenny to v6 squeeze)
	  for reason I haven't identified. Without upgrade, test log is
	  full of ERROR: Couldn't send <> to GDB
	  
	  Core dump feature usage for gdb test suite need that you unplug
	  pipe to apport that most distrib have set.
	  Look in lfs/gdb if you are curious for an example how to do that.

2011-09-03 11:06  owes

	* src/rc.d/rc.pulsardsl, src/rc.d/rc.red,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Fix path used for
	  br2684ctl, fixes using pulsar DSL.
	  Tweak use of debugging in rc.pulsardsl.

