	* lfs/squid-langpack: Was copying errors into errors.ipcop, not
	  only the directories under errors

2011-05-13 21:52  gespinasse

	* lfs/squid-langpack, updates/1.9.20/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.20,
	  updates/1.9.20/information.xml: Wrong version committed
	  There is a more recent pack with 20110512

2011-05-13 21:42  gespinasse

	* lfs/squid-langpack: Update another time langpack.
	  Thank to Melanie Osl for the info
	  
	  Tweak our build, so the exact list of installed files is build
	  everytime
	  
	  We should more use tar --no-same-owner --no-same-permissions on
	  unpacking
	  
	  Enhance a few comments
	  
	  On the double loop, remove the 2 tests
	  The first test -d should never fail as we remove the files on top
	  of uncompressed files.
	  
	  The second test -f, I would prefer if the loop fail instead of
	  skipping silently a directory.
	  So we will really know if there is now a directory there.
	  
	  We should do better than have twice 6.4 MB of uncompressed text
	  for squid error messages.
	  I don't know how, maybe keep the unused lnaguages files
	  compressed, that require only 2 x 110 kB.

2011-05-13 12:25  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/cdrtools,
	  config/rootfiles/common/xorriso, lfs/cdrom, lfs/cdrtools,
	  lfs/xorriso, make.sh: Change from cdrtools to xorriso.
	  I know cdrtools-3.0 exist, but even that does not build correctly
	  with make-3.82 and 3.01 is alpha4 or beta version.
	  Esoteric INS_BASE=/usr does not work anymore, everything is
	  installed under /opt.
	  
	  Instead xorriso build just fine, did not have scary warning that
	  make has a bug since 1988
	  
	  And xorriso will allow us to build just one image for usb and
	  cdrom boot.

2011-05-13 08:26  gespinasse

	* lfs/linux: 2.6.32.40

2011-05-13 08:10  gespinasse

	* lfs/file: file-5.07

2011-05-13 08:08  gespinasse

	* lfs/bc, lfs/diffutils, lfs/gawk, lfs/gdb, lfs/gettext, lfs/sed,
	  lfs/texinfo, lfs/which: Just more PKG_NAME usage

2011-05-13 07:32  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/apache, lfs/apache,
	  updates/1.9.20/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.20,
	  updates/1.9.20/information.xml, updates/1.9.20/setup: Upgrade
	  apache httpd to 2.2.18

2011-05-11 17:48  gespinasse

	* lfs/bash, updates/1.9.20/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.20,
	  updates/1.9.20/information.xml: Upgrade bash-4.2 to patch10
	  
	  I choose to directly load patches from bash site instead of using
	  accumulated patch from LFS after patch 7.
	  - that's simple to write too
	  - LFS sometime disagree to update bash patch
	  - easier to test individual patch if need come a day with a
	  broken patch
	  
	  I added the hack to fix bash rootfile list.
	  
	  We probably could more use simply expanded variables on makefiles
	  (those with :=)

2011-05-10 17:45  eoberlander

	* langs/bg_BG/ipcop.po, langs/list_progress,
	  updates/1.9.20/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.20: Updates from Language
	  Database (bg_BG).

2011-05-08 10:52  eoberlander

	* langs/es_UY/ipcop.po, langs/list_progress,
	  updates/1.9.20/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.20: Updates from Language
	  Database (es_UY).

2011-05-08 08:10  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/arch_i486/binutils, lfs/binutils: Another way to
	  ease cairo recompilation, suppress binutils .la files
	  We should really remove all .la files that other distrib
	  (Fedora/Debian) remove.
	  The issue is on libtools and .la files make libtools do bad
	  things 99% of the time.

2011-05-08 08:06  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/gdb, lfs/gdb: Add -g to CFLAGS, this
	  reduce the error count, particulary when gdb test gdb.
	  
	  I could have build gdb more static. There is some issues but that
	  work using
	  CFLAGS+=-U_FORTIFY_SOURCE and using LDFLAGS+='-static'
	  But there is still some lib gdb depend like ncurses that will
	  stay shared.
	  So I stopped to build static, so stripped gdb is a bit smaller.
	  
	  Tweak our gcc specs to not compile hardened the test suite. This
	  fix pie errors tests and some other.
	  That's ugly but the only way I find. Some tests don't use CFLAGS,
	  but some do, so unsetting hardening from CFLAGS not always work.
	  
	  Remove the tests we are not interested to cut time to build and
	  log (and a few errors)
	  
	  Strip gdb at end of build, as the static build size with -g is 15
	  MB.
	  
	  Stop running make install as that replace our binutils
	  lib{bdf,opcode}.a and install another time the .la files that
	  made cairo not happy on recompilation.

2011-05-07 15:25  gespinasse

	* lfs/squid-langpack: New squid langpack needed
	  
	  Clean the makefile replacing some spaces with tab
	  
	  Due to the special hack in comp_md5.pl, we probably need to
	  include all files in update.

