	* src/installer/installer.c: Fix address and netmask concatenated
	  on each network before ifconfig by replacing strcat with strcpy.
	  That could be seen on my test config with install codepath=1 (as
	  I usually only use pxe)
	  
	  I noticed that issue 23 month ago too but forgot

2011-04-03 15:56  gespinasse

	* src/installer/installer.c, src/scripts/build-rdepend: Fix
	  wich=>which typo

2011-04-03 15:43  gespinasse

	* src/installer/installer.c: At least on pxe boot, fix the can't
	  stat '/etc/dhcp-*params': No such file or directory
	  
	  A detail, interface is prefixed with eth, do the same here.
	  
	  There is another issue seen with 'install codepath=1'
	  That will fail (at least on pxe booted machine) as the string
	  with ifconfig look wrong, like
	  Running command: ifconfig eth0
	  192.168.1.120192.168.1.120192.168.1.120192.168.1.120 netmask
	  255.255.255.0255.255.255.0255.255.255.0255.255.255.0 up
	  
	  Hunting that new bug next

