	  restrictions. Settings were too strict, causing NTPd to 'loose'
	  synchronisation.

2011-02-01 19:48  eoberlander

	* langs/es_UY/install.po, langs/es_UY/ipcop.po,
	  langs/list_progress: Updates from Language Database.

2011-01-30 22:10  gespinasse

	* make.sh: Cleanup make.sh from old linux32 usage.
	  We no more compile a separate linux32 since I changed the
	  cross-compile
	  pass1. On x86_64, we rely on host linux32 until util-linux is
	  compiled

2011-01-30 13:04  gespinasse

	* config/install/init-mini-initramfs: Fix the Quiting typo
	  
	  Shorten the sleep and modify the message as it may happen more
	  than once
	  When you have
	  unhardened vmlinuz properly build with 'CC_STACKPROTECTOR is not
	  set'
	  normal vmlinuz and modules build with CC_STACKPROTECTOR=y
	  
	  on floppy boot, kernel modules will fail to insmod with 'Invalid
	  module format'
	  
	  So we need the same STACKPROTECTOR setting everytime or rebuild
	  the modules for floppy only.
	  But STACKPROTECTOR is what cause the compressed kernel to be 100
	  kB bigger and overflow the boot floppy size.

2011-01-30 11:17  gespinasse

	* lfs/initramfs, lfs/usb-key, lfs/zlib: As we use our build bash
	  there, replace seq with bash>=3.00 range syntax a la {1..7}
	  That will avoid the cost of a subprocess for seq

2011-01-29 09:24  owes

	* lfs/linux: non hardened vmlinuz only needed when building floppy
	  images

2011-01-28 22:00  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/linux-atm, lfs/linux-atm,
	  updates/1.9.18/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.18,
