	  config/rootfiles/common/tzdata, lfs/glibc, lfs/tzdata, make.sh:
	  Add tzdata compilation
	  The for loop was borrowed to ubuntu tzdata compilation log
	  because I didn't find where Debian put that.
	  
	  Remove /usr/share/zoneinfo after glibc installation, so we could
	  track those files with tzdata
	  
	  As suggest by Olaf, copy now etc/locatime to cache, and during
	  glibc compilation from cache to tools or chroot etc/localtime
	  This is much simplier, and less likely broken.
	  
	  I find why glibc-2.11.2 didn't have pacificnew, that did not
	  compile at that time in glibc-2.11

