2010-11-07 18:58  eoberlander

	* langs/da_DK/install.po, langs/da_DK/ipcop.po,
	  langs/es_ES/ipcop.po, langs/es_UY/ipcop.po, langs/sv_SE/ipcop.po,
	  updates/1.9.18/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.18: Updates from Language
	  Database.

2010-11-07 09:53  gespinasse

	* lfs/strip, make.sh: Move make.sh toolchain strippping entirely to
	  lfs/strip as make.sh is too big
	  Plus some rm instructions were made on each side against the same
	  files.
	  
	  Remade toolchain strip each time toolchain is build (easiest way
	  with ./make.sh toolchain).
	  That's easier to adjust removed files
	  
	  Remove files before stripping look more logical
	  Remove too ccache man page
	  Remove more perl CGI*, Test*, Pod* as that work the same for our
	  need
	  
	  Use same stripping rules for libs as debian
	  --strip-debug for static libs
	  --remove-section=.comment --remove-section=.note --strip-unneeded
	  for the others
	  That will show shared libs stripped, that was not the case with
	  --strip-debug only.
	  
	  Strip strip binary as that spare 3 MB (uncompressed)
	  Strip ccache
	  
	  Use standard syntax for find -exec : {} \; and not '{}' ';'
	  
	  Size decrease from 37 to 35 MB

2010-11-07 08:53  owes

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl: Using intrapositioned negation
	  throws a warning, so start using extrapositioned negation.
	  '--option ! this' should be '! --option this'

2010-11-07 08:29  owes

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl: Don't add the rules twice, 1 rule
	  is sufficient ;-)

