	  That happen frequently with bad and old media, dust ...

2010-04-26 23:14  gespinasse

	* lfs/initramfs: Mostly the end of this batch of changes
	  
	  Adjust initramfs build to use xz compressed floppy images
	  
	  Remove the acenic hack as there is now plenty enought places for
	  all nic drivers in 1 floppy
	  
	  Shift parted / libparted to root-2 floppy, this let 200 kB
	  compressed free on root-1.
	  (maybe go back to this but I didn't test)
	  
	  Use the macro to list files with size for mini-initramfs

2010-04-26 23:02  gespinasse

	* config/kernel/kernel.config.i486,
	  config/rootfiles/arch_i486/linux: Activate
	  CONFIG_OPTIMIZE_INLINING
	  This make the kernel a bit smaller
	  
	  Change some crypto code to be build as module, so vmlinuz is
	  smaller again.
	  This let us 33 kb free on floppy (with splash image include
	  again)
	  
	  Everything look to work for me, but this was more install-centric
	  than something else.

2010-04-26 22:57  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/arch_i486/xz-embedded, lfs/xz-embedded, make.sh:
	  Add zx-embedded
	  Now floppy root-1,root-2, scsi, network could be more efficiently
	  compressed
	  This let us a bit of confort in term of free space
	  (we could even keep strace on floppy)

