	  Add comment how to use the shared lib and reduce with mklibs

2010-04-26 20:19  gespinasse

	* lfs/slang: Go back using standard CFLAGS, not need to use
	  something special.
	  
	  Comment how to use shared lib and reduce them with mklibs
	  Code is not smaller for the installer as only installer is
	  linked.
	  So only compile the static lib as before

2010-04-26 19:35  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/zlib, lfs/zlib: Add what was missing to
	  reduce zlib shared with mklibs
	  No more 'No pic file found ... copying'
	  Instead
	  /lib//libz.so.1 80003L
	  /installer/initramfs/lib/libz.so.1-so 70822L
	  /installer/initramfs/lib/libz.so.1-so-stripped 60428L
	  
	  No mandatory, but this should save 10 kb (before compression)
	  
	  Documentation say it is needed to compile the static lib with
	  -fPIC.
	  But as we compile with -fPIE, that look to be enought.

