2010-04-17 13:32  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/gettext, lfs/gettext: Compile less for
	  gettext as we use only a small portion.
	  --wihtout-include-gettext is what every distrib compiling against
	  libc use.
	  
	  That's obvious we don't need static lib, support for java,
	  openmp, emacs
	  We do not include libasprintf, so do not compile that part
	  
	  Not so sure for --without-include-regex
	  I have run a full compilation with all tests without any changes
	  in the result
	  
	  Remove the .la files, Fedora, Ubuntu do that.
	  Remove the examples directory, so there is less files in the list

