2010-04-08 05:44  gespinasse

	* lfs/gzip: Fix gl_cv_func_printf_directive_n=no removed by
	  accident

2010-04-07 18:11  gespinasse

	* lfs/autoconf, lfs/bash, lfs/coreutils, lfs/diffutils,
	  lfs/findutils, lfs/gawk, lfs/grep, lfs/gzip, lfs/m4, lfs/make,
	  lfs/patch, lfs/sed, lfs/tar, lfs/texinfo, lfs/util-linux-ng,
	  make.sh: Compile tar just after xz on toolchain.
	  That's simplier to use xz package if tar host does not support xz
	  
	  Switch to .xz package when available (and after xz has been
	  compiled, so not glibc)
	  This may trigger recompilation once because lfs file has been
	  updated.
	  
	  Use --disable-nls to minimize toolchain package size
	  
	  You could find package where --disable-nls produce a change with
	  find build_i486/tools_i486/share/locale -name *.mo -exec basename
	  {} \; | sort | uniq

