	* config/etc/modprobe.d, config/etc/modprobe.d/aliases.conf,
	  config/etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf,
	  config/etc/modprobe.d/local.conf, config/etc/modules.conf,
	  config/rootfiles/common/stage2, lfs/initramfs, lfs/stage2,
	  updates/1.9.11/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.11, updates/1.9.11/setup: Turns
	  out that module blacklisting is not working (anymore), probably
	  because udev is not reading/using /etc/modules.conf.
	  Switch to the 'new' method of using *.conf files in
	  /etc/modprobe.d
	  
