2010-01-12 18:44  owes

	* config/rootfiles/common/misc-progs,
	  config/rootfiles/common/usb_modeswitch, lfs/misc-progs,
	  lfs/usb_modeswitch, make.sh, src/scripts/usb_modeswitch.sh,
	  updates/1.9.11/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.11: Add usb_modeswitch for
	  switching 3G devices from cd/disk to modem mode.
	  Since we do not have TCL, I have taken a slightly different
	  approach.
	  
	  Find the device you want to switch in /etc/usb_modeswitch.conf
	  and remove the comments.
	  Calling usb_modeswitch should then 'switch' the device. Later
	  device pull/plug and reboots will take care of the switching
	  automatically.
	  modprobe usbserial with proper vendor and product codes is needed
	  at least once.

