	  SUID wrapper for rc.red.
	  This allows us to drop suid handling from Perl, which is supposed
	  to be deleted
	  in some future Perl version anyway.

2009-12-17 20:41  owes

	* config/arch/i486/extlinux.conf,
	  config/arch/i486/syslinux-fdinitrd.cfg,
	  config/arch/i486/syslinux-serial.cfg,
	  config/arch/i486/syslinux.cfg: If we use loglevel=4 instead of
	  quiet the kernel will boot quietly, but ext- ,pxe- and syslinux
	  will show progress (using dots) of kernel loading and unpacking.
	  This avoids the 'silence' where a user may think nothing is
	  happening.

