	* lfs/atl2: Fix building on Sparc, same as we do for several other
	  kernel related packages.

2009-11-28 17:45  owes

	* lfs/stage2: /opt or /var/opt are not used, so it should be safe
	  to remove opt.

2009-11-27 20:57  owes

	* lfs/kbd: kbd compilation breaks on Sparc because of compiler
	  warning.
	  Report:
	  http://www.ipcop-forum.de/forum/viewtopic.php?f=22&t=25766
	  
	  (temporary) fix same as in Gentoo: http://bugs.gentoo.org/289589

2009-11-23 19:19  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/stage2, lfs/stage2, make.sh: Remove to
	  the need to have /usr/src writable by everyone.
	  This fix some coreutils-8.1 tests with perl when
	  /usr/src/<package> is
	  added to the PATH
	  
	  Now /usr/src is owned by build user on toolchain stage.
	  On stage2, ownership is passed to root
	  
	  On stage2, don't fake to create directories like
	  /bin,/dev,/proc,/sys
	  already created by make.sh.
	  Similary, bash symlink need to exist before stage2 run, so that's
	  unneeded to try there.
	  
	  /us/local/src is not used, removed
	  Do we need /opt ?
	  
	  Reorder stage2 rootfile and add a few missing files
	  
	  We no more need to create /etc in make.sh, that's a remaining
	  part when
	  /etc was mounted

2009-11-23 14:11  owes

	* config/rootfiles/common/cgilib, lfs/cgilib: Drop cgilib.
	  Used to be required for rrdtool. Not build and used for some time
	  now.

